caption: Amazing food and fast service!
Waiter was very minimal with service, Introduction was "do you know what to order" No one check how's everything. Server needs a review of performance. Nwy food was delicious!
We had the spicy tan tan ramen and it was very good.   Not as spicy as I was hoping for but very flavorful. Would definitely offer it again.
The tonkotsu ramen was very oily and hard to eat. Their gyoza was also a huge disappointment compared to even local chinese takeout.

Ramen was horrible.  The broth is like a thick gravy.  They use coconut milk.  It'd be a solid at room temperature.  How is that called Ramen, and why wouldn't they at least mention the coconut milk on the menu?  Plus, they have 2 TV's that basically no seats face.  Very confusing.
Loved their acai bowl! 🤙
Great food. Great price. Right off the beach. Delicious ramen
Excellent poke. Fast service.
Delivery lady/driver went to the wrong place, refused to take directions to come to mine and cancelled my order after being 15 minutes late. RUDE ! Will not order again and don’t recommend you do.
Amazing food, for ramen or sushi, this is a must stop in.

The service is okay, their menu is not special, very normal Japanese menu, the price is Waikiki price, the atmosphere at the restaurant is pretty nice. the food is very delicious, I love their taste, but I need bigger portion.  Got  Pork gyoza and Sticky ribs, they are pretty good. Next time wanna try Karaage.
Very rude personnel and food is not worth the price. Ordered breakfast and harsh browns were frozen. Avoid if possible!

We had a quite beautiful night sitting on the lovely deck, while we enjoyed our Mai Thai and Frosted Beer. We absolutely enjoyed our Sushi, and Tonkatsu. The staff was polite and made us feel safe with all the standard COVID precautions.  #greatdatenightspot
Great food. Spicy Tan Tan is phenomenal
Went here for dinner last night and ordered veggie rolls and veggie Ramen.   Absolutely fantastic service, drinks and food.   Definitely would recommend and go back.

Tonkotsu with an order of chashu and a large extra noodles. My husband said every time we go out for ramen, order this dish for him. We would have to eat at Momosan Ramen & Sake- Waikiki every time we eat ramen. This involves moving to Hawai’i. Very, very good. California Roll. Real crab flakes apart with fragrant wasabi. Fresh. Soft Shell Bao. We had carry away due to the COVID-19 pandemic. Not really- we got out of the hotel late and it would have been impolite to the Chef. But it is true that due to the COVID-19 pandemic my husband and I can just walk up and order the best food we have had in Waikiki after 5 days. Thank you Momosan. Karaage. I’m guessing the Ka is for go because the twice fried potato starch battered chicken thigh tastes Korean. What does Korean taste like? The sauce is sweet and spicy and tangy. You must order this chicken. I don’t know what Korean tastes like- that’s cannibalism.
Peaceful, shady cafe just steps from Waikiki Beach. The Tonkotsu was filling and delicious, and the staff was friendly and courteous throughout.

Was lured in by the happy hour sign. Tried the spicy dan dan and a frozen lager. Unfortunately, the frozen lager was not on happy hour, but the waiter made sure I was ok with that. Maybe on a hot day, it's worth $7. I'm glad I tried it, but would stick to the happy hour beer in the future. The spicy dan dan was very good. The waiter warned me to take it slowly and not slurp it like ramen, because the spice would hit me. Despite the warning, I did manage to make my eyes water a couple of times. Would definitely get it again. Had a sliver of a view of the surfers across the street. Also got a happy hour beer. Total with 20% tip was about $30.
Great Ramen
My favorite part about this spot was the outside seating that includes comfortable benches and large tables to sit and chat with friends.

Went here for a quick happy hour beer and try some grinds from an iron chef. No happy hour food truly, but got to try the frozen beer. It indeed was refreshing and it’s “head” held up. Frothy and almost like a soft meringue, it was a nice experience.
Amazing service.  The Kirin Slurpies are legit.
Tan tan noodles was awesome, the pork ribs were amazing! I'm definitely going back!
Excellent service, mediocre food.

(Translated by Google) I couldn't take a photo of Tantan-myeon, pork ramen, draft beer, but I ate sushi The staff was also pleasant and it was nice to be able to eat at the outdoor table. It's Waikiki right across the street, so I was able to eat this and go to see the sunset right away... It's a house where people are always waiting, so I went to eat right before 6 o'clock..  (Original) 탄탄면이랄 돈코츠라멘,생맥주,사진은 먹느라 못찍었지만 초밥 먹었는데요 직원들도 유쾌하고 야외 테이블에서 먹을 수 있어서 좋았습니다. 길건너 바로 와이키키라 이거 먹고 바로 선셋보러 갈 수 있었죵.. 사람이 늘 기다리는 집이라 6시전에가서 바로 먹었습니다..

Best miso ramen on the island ♡ Friendly, knowledgeable & attentive staff. Great food! Love the open air seating, it is cozy & we could see waikiki beach from our table. Most importantly you feel the aloha spirit, even though covid laws restrict us. As kama'aina we know to expect higher prices in waikiki, but it's worth it! The portion size was perfect for a sit down meal, nice to be free from takeout containers afterwards, makes it easy to go shopping or swimming or... I suggest grab some friends who like to share & sample what everyone else has ordered. I can't wait to go back with a D2 so I can try the sake.

Absolutely fantastic. Went here three times in three days and had a bit of everything on the menu. Food was CLEARLY being prepared fresh each day and made to order. We had shrimp tempura sushi that was piping hot and made right when we ordered. Japanese fried chicken that was perfectly done and flavorful. Spicy ramen tan tan was exquisite. Gyoza (potstickers) were amazingly fresh, some of the best I’ve ever had. All of it was just great. Also, they have the perfect patio to space out and feel very safe dining during COVID times. Will certainly come back next trip.
Noodle was warm and salty.  Noodles were too soft for me and size was small.  Gyoza was fine but the scallion sauce was also salty.

Friendly Staff. They follow the covid standards very well. Not many gluten-free options aside from the gluten-free Tamari soy sauce. Ramen broth is not gluten-free. I recommend pairing the cloudy unfiltered sparkling sake with the nigiri or sushi. The Tuna was our unexpected favorite.

Everything was absolutely delicious. Surprised that it wasn't packed. Went back a second time a couple of days later. The ramen set is the way to go. 1st time had the pork belly bao and spicy tan tan ramen and beer with frozen foam. Second time had the popcorn shrimp app and the softshell crab bao and spicy tan tan.
Great food, and even better service.  We have been there twice on this trip.
The veggie ramen was not good. Boyfriend liked the Tan tan ramen. Good for regular ramen, not for vegetarians.
Quality food with quality ingredients.  The dishes are a little greasy, however.  - returning customer.
I wish they had more options in chicken and beef.
Great place, excellent food!  Would definitely go back.  No complaints with any of our orders
Nice place, good service, good food, outdoor seating, casual dining.
Excellent food, their Waguyu loco moco is spectacular, a refined and wonderful rendition of a local dish.
Bra, that Tantan with the coconut curry is on point!
Amazing food! Highly recommend. Great outdoor space, cozy and nice! The service is super fast! Everything was nice and fresh.
This place was pretty good.
Let's see what this sushi like
Food was ok but expensive for what you get. Frozen beer is fun. Service is slow.

So impressed with breakfast today everything was so organized and cleaned management was there working during the Coronavirus we were out supporting local before the two-week shutdown we were grateful they were there and we will definitely be back the management and the food is top-notch
My favorite restaurant in Waikiki!

We had a lot of good food on Oahu, but this small spot on the strip was arguably the best. We were very impressed with everything the server brought out, but we were blown away by the cold ramen. Can’t wait to go back!

Momosan is a must try for ramen lovers! The broth is rich in flavor and so so so creamy! The shoyu sliced are delicious! And the chashu don is amazing. Don't miss out on this lovely ramen house on the beach strip! Beaitiful scenery and delicious!
Tantan is amazing!

Walked in for lunch based on a recommendation from my hotel concierge. Requested a small bowl of Tonkotsu ramen and chicken karaage, and they made it into a special Lunch Set for me.  I discovered that I don't like my karaage sweet, so next time I'll get the sauce on the side. The ramen was phenomenal, and so I recommend trying this place out. Service was outstanding and attentive. (Thanks Jaimie K!)
The best ramen in Honolulu!!!
The duck tacos, sake and ramen were delicious, and our server Ryan was the absolute best! We'll definitely be going back.
Not the best ramen that I had. Small portions and there were more soybeans than noodles.
Dropped in for a late night ramen fix. Nice environment in the breezy outdoor. Great food for sure. Service was a little slow, our server was a little distracted at times when we did need him
Excellant, unique selections. Great staff.
Good ramen noodles, great service. Would come here again.
Very fun to try something new. Excellent flavors, absolutely loved the spring rolls. Skewers were fantastic, and the ramen, delicious. Would definitely recommend. I love Waikiki.

The Duck Ramen bowl [with duck broth!] was absolutely fantastic.  Like, it was so beautifully done.  It was refreshing to get a proper portion of meat while eating out after spending a year in Australia.  Every bite of the generous serving of duck breast was like candy, the broth light and clean, and the noodles were cooked perfectly.  Big fan of the outdoor seating as well.  If ever in Waikiki again, I will definitely be returning.

I was excited to try this ramen place since it’s connection to Japanese iron chef Morimoto.  However, as a Japanese and ramen die hard fan myself, I was very disappointed with the quality of the ramen.  I don’t think this place is specialized for ramen at all.  I ordered tonkatsu ramen, and the quality and the taste of the ramen broth is not good.  The quantity of the ramen itself is small for the price they charged.  Ippudo, Oni, and Santoku ramens have better quality and taste than this.  In summary:  I don’t recommend this place at all for ramen.  It’s one of the worst ramen I ever tried in my 20 years experience.
The best ramen i have ever eat
Delicious ramen.
The happy hour for beer is the best thing they have, if you're looking for GOOD ramen go to yokocho instead

(Translated by Google) Waikiki Japanese Ramen and Sake Restaurant. Opens twice a day for lunch and dinner. In the evening, it is closed around 10 o'clock. I can see a lot of Japanese because they are Japanese. The location is right next to Waikiki Resort and the opening hours are not very long. Japanese menus and foods are the main menu, and you can enjoy simple alcoholic beverages. The restaurant has an open-air seat indoors and outside. Hawaii has a very good tip culture. Since the whole island is a tourist destination, the tips are very hard for all service sectors. Tips already have a tip on your bill. Present 17,18,19% and respond accordingly. I think the tip culture is a bit higher than other American cities, and I need to know about Koreans. If you don't tip it, it's a little angry. Anyway, this restaurant is a Japanese restaurant, so it is recommended for those who like Japanese style.  (Original) 와이키키 일본식 라멘 및 사케 전문 음식점. 하루 점심시간 저녁시간 두번 문을 엽니다. 저녁에는 10시정도 문을 닫습니다. 일본계여서인지 일본인도 많이 볼수가 있습니다. 위치는 와이키키 리조트 바로 옆에 있으며, 영업시간이 매우 긴 편이 아닙니다. 일본식의 메뉴와 음식들이 주를 이루고 있으며, 간단한 주류를 즐기기 좋습니다. 식당은 실내와 외부 노천 자리가 있습니다. 하와이는 팁문화가 좀 쎈편입니다. 섬 전체가 관광유흥지이기 때문에 모든 서비스업종에 대해서는 팁이 아주 쎄게 부르는 편입니다. 팁은 계산서에 이미 팁을 정해달리는 문구가 있습니다. 17,18,19%를 제시하고 여기에 응대해서 체크해주면 됩니다. 다른 미국 도시들에 비해서 팁문화가 좀 높다고 생각이되며, 한국사람들에 대해서는 이를 주지해야할 필요가 있을것같습니다. 팁을 주지 않으면 약간의 화를 내는 얼굴입니다. 어떻든 이 식당은 일본 식당이기 때문에 일본식을 좋아하는 사람들은 권장할만합니다.

The ramen was especially delicious! We also tried the 5 year saki which was to dye for! The staff is also very nice and the cooks look like they are having a very fun time while making your food delicious!

We came here just for happy hours beer because they promote $3 Kirin.  Told us we needed to order something small because beer was cheap. So we said ok, we were in the mood for appetizers. Appetizers were meh... and they didn’t really care to serve use just because we ordered beer, sake, and appetizers. We waited a long time for drinks and appetizers. Sad because this place looked promising but was a disappointment. We wanted to try the ramen because it looked good but after appetizers we  changed our minds.

The ramen is pretty good. The drink specials are nice too during happy hour. They also have quite an exrensive menu outside of just ramen.
Food was decent the ramen was good. Tonkotsu ramen was flavourful and the pork was delicious. I recommend checking this place out if you're looking for ramen but the service can be greatly improved.

Not vegetarian friendly and pescatarian options are slim....on the beach! Dined in last week, we got 1 starter before a wait on our beer... Then the count it.. 1 skewered shrimp... I ate infront of my guest ..Service was awful and one entree never came out. Our server asked us nearly an hour later "if we still wanted it" OK .. Of all our vacation meals this was the worst.
Every dish is delicious and creative. Must try their appetizers. Hamburger steak and softshell bao are both good. Highly recommand.

Very friendly staff and right off of Kalakaua. So many options to choose. I tried something new which was the noodles that you dip in the broth. A little difficult to master at first. I would visit again
very expensive but delicious ramen

Nice taste and environment. Price was reason able consisting the location.

I will never eat just regular Ramen again. So good.

Disappointing... and also not vegetarian friendly at all. I'm a fan of Morimoto and have been to many of his restaurants. Usually you can go to one of his restaurants expecting some kind of traditional Japanese food with personal/modern/Western twist, and dishes usually are sooo good. I think that was my expectation going to Momosan, but I didn't get any of those things... Ramen was very bland, drinks are just okay and there are almost no vegetarian options! (my wife is vegetarian).

My husband and I dined in your restaurant last week. The food was fabulous! However, the service could have greatly been improved. My cocktail took a long time and I had to send it back the first time it came out as it was incorrectly made. And our food took exponentially long. What a great menu selection it has, each dish we had was delicious however the portions are small and quite pricey. The Ramen noodles provides a more substantial meal at a reasonable cost. But the food you do receive is excellent, just be prepared to order more than you normally would. I tried the frozen beer. Only the head of the beer is actually frozen so you have to suck off most of the froth before you can drink anything. This wasn't my cup of tea but once I got to the beer it was good, and it kept my beer cool. I would just stick to the standard beer. Otherwise a great setting with great food, recommended.

Beautiful food and really helpful staff who talked us through the menu. Not being the most experienced of using chop sticks the waiter almost knew our wishes, chuckling as he left to retrieve some cutlery.

This place is great. Went during lunch time and was pleasantly pleased. The service was great.  I hat the duck tacos and pork belly ramen and it was beyond what I expected. The pork belly was crispy and seasoned to perfection.  My wife had the spicy curry pork and she loved it. The spice was not too hot but definetly there. Together is was 46 bucks which is typical for Waikiki at this level of food. If you are like me and want to have a real ramen experience this would be a great place to go.

Nice spot for ramen. We enjoyed the tonkatsu ramen. Broth had a kick to it and the pork had a sweet flavor and almost resembled bacon. Price was a bit on the high side but this is tourist central and beach front so its expected to pay a little more for views and atmosphere. Im spoiled and used to my ramen being about less than 10$ where as here it was like 15+ dollars.  Still good tho.

The ramen was fine but if your expecting Japanese authentic then look elsewhere. The softshell crab bao was delicious, as well as the sorbet and cheesecake. I highly recommend sticking with appetizers and desserts over the ramen when dining.
Great food and sake. Can't wait to go again.
Karaage is good!
Their noodles are good, when visiting trying it out.
Portion size was accurate to Japanese portions. Food was amazing. Service was friendly and quick. Reasonably priced for the area and what you’re getting.

Very tasty Tonkotsu (pictured) and attentive service. I also had the veggie spring rolls, the ramen and rolls were very hot, be careful and wait a bit so you don’t scorch your tongue. The atmosphere is elegant as it is mainly an outdoor restaurant with nice decor and string lights. I ate here around 9:30pm so it was a bit lively with music and a decent size loud crowd. Key point..McDonald’s is across the street which may sway your or your kids appetites! 🍔

Quality ramen on Waikiki beach.  Restaurant interior has a large bar and edm for a club vibe, but step outside to the patio seating for a more chill vibe.  Roasted duck tacos were great, crisp shells, duck fat and a light sauce. Tonkotu ans butabara Ramens were also good: soup, noodles, and toppings were all high quality. The 牛骨 gyukotsu was my favorite but the kale has no business in ramen other than to signal that this bowl is different so it costs more.  Prices are high but so is everything on the waikiki beach strip.
Very limited vegetarian options, and not willing to be flexible (e.g. not willing to make ramen without broth to avoid chicken/beef).
fab foods
Had the duck ramen...best ramen ever. Fast and friendly service.

Food was tasty but very small, pricey portions. All entree's were appetizer size. If you want to just sample some fancy food it's great. If you want to have an actual meal there are many other spots that have great food with great value.
Head chef was at the bar doing expo, he was amazing and the food was even better. Great job all around.

First of all, I just love the atmosphere. Outside seating, yet kind of quiet, and real casual.  I had the butabara ramen.  Wonderful broth - like having a roast chicken. We also had the mimiga.  Totally addictive.  It's like having bacon fries. Other must haves are the duck fat French fries and karaage.  We also liked the duck taco and soft shell crab bun.  I would have given 5 stars if not for the skewers.  They were just ok. Nothing wrong with them, just nothing special.
Excellent food and the staff was friendly.

Excellent ramen, great service. Our server explained several sakes and made recommendations. Excellent recommendations too, for someone who doesn't care for sake much. The frozen kirin was good. At hh, it's a great price too. The menu items we tried were delicious.
The food here was amazing. You HAVE to try their Mai Tai. It is absolutely amazing!  Thank you guys for having such good food and customer service.
Quality ramen noodles and variety of small dishes that work greatly with beers. Happy Hour 5-7:00, Frozen beer $3.00, Kirin draft $2.00  Parking is varidated.

I was really excited to try this place as I was staying in the hotel. It didn’t live up to expectation unfortunately. But this may be because I came just before closing at 9.58pm ( they close at 10) service was great but could tell they weren’t excited to see me in.  The broth was really fatty and I could tell this was due to me coming in so late they probably had the left over broth and served it. Would of preferred if they told me they were closed if they couldn’t serve a good bowl.  It was so greasy and fatty when I drank out of my glass the fat froze on my cup of water. Would maybe come back just to have a proper experience.
Friendly staff and nice presentation but mild flavors and lack of spice don't do it for me. The frozen beer is interesting but completely gimmicky. The location is nice.
Wow! What a pleasant surprise 😍 Food, drink and service were incredible!

Typically speaking, you order ramen maybe with a side of Gyoza if it’s in Japan, and you don’t linger there and leave promptly after you finish your ramen. Chef Morimoto breaks classic rules of Ramen restaurants and suggests an untraditional dining style that suits perfect to spend a night in Waikiki. This place is where you MUST order some sides before getting ramen, otherwise you don’t get the most out of your experience at Momosan. If you’re ramen savvy, make sure you order the ramen that is recommended by the restaurant. I ordered Tokyo Chicken, which was meh. The noodle was clearly Sun noodle kind, and the bowl was full of toppings but they were also unbalanced with the portion of noodles. Broth wasn’t anything special either, so I must come back and try different ones. On the other hand, gyoza and beef tongues were the winners of the night — beef tongues were thick and flavorful, much better than beef tongue from some cheap Yakiniku places. Don’t go there if you can’t splurge for trying several different appetizers. If what you’re used to is a simple in-and-out ramen dining style, do yourself a favor and go Wagaya or Golden Pork to avoid the chaos and ambivalence in Waikiki. Great service, free parking with the restaurant validation!
